ct teams to help maintain a deep understanding of Fortanix products, core technology, and customer applications. Market Feedback. Continuously gather product and market feedback to guide new products. Customer Success. Ensure customers and partners are getting the most from their investment in Fortanix, creating strong references, renewals, and opportunities for upsell. Requirements MUST BE BASED IN US preferably Mid Atlantic, North Central, South Central or West Coast. Must have 5+ years of experience as an SE or Solutions Architect for enterprise IT security and infrastructure. Must have experience in complex technical enterprise sales processes, including $1M+ deals. Knowledge of programming or scripting languages (e.g., Python, Bash, etc.). Understanding of HSM and various crypto interfaces (PKCS#11, CAPI, CNG, JCE, etc.). Experience with HSM from another company is a plus. Understanding of KMS interfaces (KMIP, REST API, etc.). Experience with a KMIP appliance is a plus. Familiarity with HSM and KMS in the cloud (AWS CloudHSM, AWS KMS, Google KMS, Azure KeyVault, IBM KeyProtect, etc.) Understanding of use cases of HSM and KMS (Database TDE, TLS termination, Blockchain, secure manufacturing, etc.) Comfortable working in a roll-up your sleeves, get your hands dirty start-up environment. Experience selling to Global 1000 / Financial Services companies. Experience working with Strategic partners and system integrators in complex environment. Strong consultative selling and technical collaboration skills. Excellent written and oral communications skills. Strong collaboration skills to engage both external partners and internal team. BA/BS in a technical field; CISSP, Security+, other security-focused certifications. Government Security clearance is a plus. Benefits Competitive compensation plan with significant upside potential Medical, dental and vision insurance; 401k Friendly, collaborative culture A chance at shaping the future of cloud security ", 
